        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BR>"Welcome back to _Are you pulling this out of your ass?_ --"</P><P>"Today our guest is a necromancer. Israfel, what rumors and innuendo do you believe to true?"</P><P><BR>Well, John, based on my tests with several group compositions in EverQuest, I believe that pets will be counted as a group member for experience calculations if they are at the top of a mob's hate list when it dies (which does not implicitly mean that they outdamaged every other individual group member, but that is the easiest case to prove). This mainly affects groups that use a pet or pets at the primary tank. When you are soloing, you are a group of one.</P><P></P><P>"Thanks Israfel, but are you sure that didn't come from the magic ass they take IPO prices and the list of bands slated to become popular?"</P><P>Nothing is certain John, but that's my analysis. I invite everyone to do their own tests and decide for themselves. ShowEQ experiences reports are accurate to the best of anyone's knowledge.</P><P>"But isn't that ... Cheating?"</P><P>Yes and no, it's only cheating if you use it gain an unfair advantage over other players. I refuse to live or play in a world I an prevented from understanding, and since the EQ client tries to hide many important game 'physics,' players are forced to use outside tools.</P><P>"Thanks, Israfel."</P><P>"On our next segment, we'll be interviewing the infamous Abashi to find out just how deep in he has to reach to get his excuses for broken code. Good night, and good will"</P><P><BR>-- <BR>Life is a zero sum game, the only way to win is not to play.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
