        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=35177&TOPIC_ID=4687&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pets+and+Experience&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Ohhhh!</P><P>Cheater, cheater, cheater!</P><P>:P</P><P>How does seq, or anything else for that matter show who has acquired the most hate.  You could go by damage done perhaps, but obviously hate is also acquired by debuffs that do no physical damage.</P><P>There must be at least 2 values involved with mob-player interaction.  Hate, which is acrued based upon damage, debuff, taunting, distance to player, player sitting down, and which is evident from which char the mob is trying to beat down.  And Damage, which seems to be primarily concerned with determining who gets the exp.</P><P>It has been pretty well proved that if the pet does more than 50% of the damage (not hate) solo, then the pet takes 50% of the exp.</P><P>It doesn't seem right to think that hate would come into play for exp determination in only the one special instance where you are grouped and have a pet.  </P><P>So the theories I have heard are that...<BR>1. If the pet outdamages the whole party, then he takes 50% of the exp before the party split.<BR>2. If the pet outdamages the whole party, then he takes 50% of the pet owner's exp after the party split.<BR>3. If the pet outdamages the whole party, then he takes 1 "share" of the exp just like an extra party member (but given the old char exp based exp split and the current lvl based exp split methods, it isn't clear how the pet's "share" would be allocated).</P><P>Theories 1 and 2 make no difference to the owner of the pet in terms of experience gained.</P><P>Anyway, someone who uses seq for multiple chars at once should be able to tell us by simply creating a L1 Nec and a L1 fighter and killing 2 mobs.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

