        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I am an exp whore, so i'm always solo. basically, the solo situation is clear: if you do more than 50% of the damage, you will get 95% or so of the xp. </P><P>a group is totally different. i spent 5 hours in pog with a group that got xp for every other kill (we felt a bit bad). at 55 the only nuke i was allowed to use was deflux, and dots were a complete waste of mana.. needless to say i wasn't outdamaging the rogue pet. at the end of the night i had less than one blue bubble, the rest of my group got 2-3 blues. i've never once heard anyone complain that their xp is slower with me and pet around, so i can only assume that pet is taking xp from me. I would guess that when you are grouped, the same rules apply as when solo. if you don't outdamage your pet you're froaked. </P><P>welcome to the only class with an xp penalty. verant, pick a testicle to suck on.</P><P><center><BR><table><tr><td><img src="http://www.cnnw.net/~snag/dave/BigSnaggy2.jpg"></td><td align=center><BR>-Snag L'puss <br><BR>55 lizard necro <br><BR>-Weirzbowskey Nerfme<br><BR>dusty 54 high elf pally<br></td></tr></table><BR></center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
