        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=35371&TOPIC_ID=4687&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Pets+and+Experience&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">By that theory Israfel, I could steal exp from 3 groups of 18 just by casting my insta-necro-summoning fairly low damage Cessation of Cor DoT spell?  Because when I cast it, the mobs definitely hate me more than anything else there.</P><P>If hate were the only concern, then debuffing classes could also KS (or PL exp) just by casting lots of no damage debuffs?  Warriors would get exp just by taunting a  mob without taking a swing, etc.  This makes me pretty sure hate and damage are tracked seperately and damage done is the usual way of determining who gets exp.</P><P>Can't say whether sitting is a hate multiplier or a fixed add in factor if already on the hate list.  I do know that for some mobs, sitting is more hateful than for others.  And also sitting can cause low greenies (those annoying SK lionesses come to mind) to figure you for fair game, where they wouldn't mess with you while standing.</P><P>As for ST clearing hate, I have been using that quite a bit as well, what I have seen seems to indicate a fixed reduction in damage done per ST, and a all or none reduction in hate from a ST.  While PLing a dru on hornets in BW, 1 ST would never give the Dru exp, 2 STs would on 1 out of 4, 3 STs would on 24 out of 25.  The hornets I was fighting have around 1800 or 2700 hps depending on the type.  There is no statistical way to get those results based on pure probability (ie. randomness) but if we presumed a fixed 1000 pt reduction in damage, then things work out a little more rationally.  In this case, the hate factor is indicated by which way the dark-feared hornet is turned.  While he hated me, he faced away when feared, after each ST he turned back towards what I believe to be his normal pathing, until the next tick of darkness, which gave me back some hate and he then turned directly away from me again.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
